  m_text: Calorie (pl. calories) is one of the units of heat, along with Joule. Hence,
    it is the reason we have calorimetry. Calorie is defined as the energy required
    to increase the temperature of one gram by one degree centigrade. Thus, calorimetry
    is defined as the science of measuring heat.
